verbose_text: It has not yet been ascertained whether the overexpression of tissue ACE2, in pathological states or induced by treatment, increases infection with SARS-CoV-2 or makes up for its deficiency to reduce cardiac, pulmonary, and renal inflammation and vasoconstriction.
evidence: ACE2, in pathological states or induced by treatment, increases infection with SARS-CoV-2 or makes up for its deficiency to reduce cardiac, pulmonary, and renal inflammation
